1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:37,960
=Episode 5=

3
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:45,520
Are you ready for it?

4
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:49,119
Wait, Yu Ming.

5
00:01:51,240 --> 00:01:51,960
I've only decided

6
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:52,759
not to divorce you for now.

7
00:01:52,759 --> 00:01:54,440
You don't have to...

8
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:54,839
You...

9
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:57,279
I... You didn't even bathe.

10
00:01:57,279 --> 00:01:58,720
It's so messy here.

11
00:02:15,079 --> 00:02:15,639
Is this

12
00:02:17,079 --> 00:02:17,639
money?

13
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:19,160
I ran it through a bill counter.

14
00:02:19,479 --> 00:02:20,160
It's all real.

15
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:35,519
I knew this would happen.

16
00:02:36,519 --> 00:02:37,320
I thought

17
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:38,720
you'd fall back.

18
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:39,959
Unexpectedly,

19
00:02:40,799 --> 00:02:42,160
you fell face down.

20
00:02:53,079 --> 00:02:54,079
Where did you get all that?

21
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,359
It was hidden in the wall.

22
00:02:55,359 --> 00:02:56,840
One of the walls was hollow inside.

23
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,639
Got it from the wall?

24
00:02:58,560 --> 00:02:59,639
No need. I'm fine.

25
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:00,679
You are so tough.

26
00:03:00,679 --> 00:03:02,160
You're much more sober than I was.

27
00:03:02,160 --> 00:03:03,320
When I found the money,

28
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:04,359
I passed out on the spot.

29
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,639
Then I woke up, saw the money,

30
00:03:05,639 --> 00:03:06,679
and passed out again.

31
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:07,600
Over and over,

32
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,239
I don't know
how many times I blacked out,

33
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,359
or for how long.

34
00:03:10,959 --> 00:03:12,479
How much in total here?

35
00:03:12,679 --> 00:03:13,600
30 million.

36
00:03:22,799 --> 00:03:23,720
Does Hong Jinkui know this?

37
00:03:25,519 --> 00:03:26,160
No.

38
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:27,239
If he knew,

39
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,679
why would he sell me the house?

40
00:03:37,079 --> 00:03:38,040
Does the former owner know this?

41
00:03:38,079 --> 00:03:38,560
No.

42
00:03:38,639 --> 00:03:39,280
I went to see her.

43
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:40,679
She said everything about this house

44
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:42,000
had nothing to do with her from then on.

45
00:03:42,079 --> 00:03:42,639
Her own words.

46
00:03:44,239 --> 00:03:44,880
Do you have...?

47
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:45,239
Yes.

48
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:51,000
You mean this?

49
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:05,480
♪Every fortune♪

50
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:08,170
♪Has its cause♪

51
00:04:08,170 --> 00:04:10,520
♪Do not mistake it♪

52
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:13,320
♪For heaven's grace♪

53
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:16,280
♪Lost in pleasure♪

54
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:18,960
♪Blind to sorrow♪

55
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:22,200
♪The lure of gold lights♪

56
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:24,960
♪The path to ruin♪

57
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:28,000
♪A fleeting taste of wealth♪

58
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,360
♪A carefree dream♪

59
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:32,720
♪Neon lights flicker♪

60
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:35,800
♪Minds drift astray♪

61
00:04:36,010 --> 00:04:38,920
♪Wine runs dry♪

62
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:41,720
♪Another night is gone♪

63
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,520
♪Yet life's burdens♪

64
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:46,960
♪Remain unresolved♪

65
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:49,120
♪A dream of fame and fortune♪

66
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:52,000
♪Blinds the hearts of many♪

67
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,560
♪Life's endless scenes♪

68
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:57,720
♪Pass in the blink of an eye♪

69
00:04:57,800 --> 00:05:00,360
♪A fleeting taste of wealth♪

70
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:02,400
♪A carefree dream♪

71
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,840
♪Neon lights flicker♪

72
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:08,120
♪Minds drift astray♪

73
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:11,720
♪Wine runs dry♪

74
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:14,000
♪Another night is gone♪

75
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,800
♪Yet life's burdens♪

76
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:18,760
♪Remain unresolved♪

77
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:21,800
♪A dream of fame and fortune♪

78
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:24,360
♪Blinds the hearts of many♪

79
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:26,920
♪Life's endless scenes♪

80
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:30,200
♪Pass in the blink of an eye♪

81
00:05:48,679 --> 00:05:49,160
I had a dream.

82
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:50,400
Me too.

83
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:54,239
So thirsty.

84
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:55,359
I'll take a sip too.

85
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:56,840
I'm a little hungry.

86
00:05:57,999 --> 00:05:59,280
If we go crazy like this,

87
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,160
will you get pregnant?

88
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:01,239
It doesn't matter. Just let it be.

89
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:02,919
With the money,
we can have as many kids as we want.

90
00:06:02,919 --> 00:06:04,200
But how do we explain this?

91
00:06:04,319 --> 00:06:05,400
We can't put it in the bank.

92
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:05,679
Right?

93
00:06:05,879 --> 00:06:06,840
Making multiple deposits won't do.

94
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:07,999
It'd trigger warnings from the bank.

95
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:08,439
Yeah.

96
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:09,400
Just say

97
00:06:09,439 --> 00:06:10,280
it was passed down

98
00:06:10,319 --> 00:06:11,359
and was dug out at home.

99
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,280
Did your ancestors use RMB notes?

100
00:06:13,439 --> 00:06:15,080
We dug out some gold ingots
and sold them.

101
00:06:15,119 --> 00:06:15,840
What floor do you live on?

102
00:06:16,879 --> 00:06:17,400
The second floor.

103
00:06:17,479 --> 00:06:17,960
Can you dig there?

104
00:06:18,479 --> 00:06:18,999
No.

105
00:06:19,239 --> 00:06:19,919
Borrowed it from a friend.

106
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:22,040
Oh sure, you happen to have a friend
with 30 million.

107
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:22,640
This won't work.

108
00:06:22,799 --> 00:06:23,559
Let's do this.

109
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:24,960
We move the money back home first.

110
00:06:24,999 --> 00:06:26,040
If we took so much money home,

111
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:26,919
would your mom handle it,

112
00:06:26,919 --> 00:06:27,760
or would my mom?

113
00:06:27,799 --> 00:06:29,040
Don't let the excitement kill them.

114
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:29,600
What can we do then?

115
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:32,040
We can't bring our money back home.

116
00:06:32,119 --> 00:06:34,239
It's like wearing fine clothes at night
when no one can see.

117
00:06:34,479 --> 00:06:35,040
What a shame!

118
00:06:36,319 --> 00:06:37,119
Let's get more sleep.

119
00:06:38,879 --> 00:06:39,999
Just have another dream.

120
00:07:33,799 --> 00:07:35,559
Miss Zhou, you know her?

121
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:38,919
Chen Zinuo,

122
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:41,200
my classmate at the University of Music,

123
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,559
Drama and Media Hanover in Germany.

124
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:44,200
Back in school,

125
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:45,280
we liked competing for the top grade.

126
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:46,640
Sometimes, she ranked first,

127
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:47,600
and sometimes, I did.

128
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:49,840
But she always outshone me.

129
00:07:51,799 --> 00:07:52,799
My advisor said my efforts

130
00:07:52,799 --> 00:07:54,239
couldn't match her natural talent.

131
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,239
No matter how
technically accurate I was,

132
00:07:56,520 --> 00:07:57,040
I could never

133
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,600
interpret the music as deeply
as she did.

134
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:00,559
So, sometimes,

135
00:08:00,559 --> 00:08:01,720
even when I won,
I wasn't happy.

136
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:04,040
I always felt like
she was letting me win.

137
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:08,559
Wait here for me.

138
00:08:16,479 --> 00:08:17,439
Why are you here?

139
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,559
I sent you many messages.

140
00:08:19,879 --> 00:08:20,760
Did you read them?

141
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,760
I just want an answer.

142
00:08:24,479 --> 00:08:25,520
Back then, I was ready

143
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:26,200
to go to Paris.

144
00:08:26,559 --> 00:08:27,640
But Dresden State Orchestra

145
00:08:27,640 --> 00:08:28,559
suddenly sent me an offer.

146
00:08:29,559 --> 00:08:30,720
Did you give that chance to me?

147
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:34,559
Your scores were better than mine.

148
00:08:35,439 --> 00:08:36,760
I didn't need you to give it to me.

149
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:40,480
All these years, I always thought

150
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:42,760
you were a principal cellist
at some orchestra.

151
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:45,919
What are you doing here in this place?

152
00:08:46,559 --> 00:08:47,520
What's wrong with this place?

153
00:08:48,679 --> 00:08:49,559
Music can just be played

154
00:08:49,559 --> 00:08:50,400
anywhere.

155
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:51,480
You can play it at a hotel,

156
00:08:51,799 --> 00:08:52,520
at an orchestra,

157
00:08:52,919 --> 00:08:53,640
at the beach,

158
00:08:53,799 --> 00:08:54,959
in the desert, or by the sea...

159
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:56,679
You can even play it on a plane.

160
00:08:57,079 --> 00:08:57,760
Is there a problem?

161
00:09:01,439 --> 00:09:01,959
Let's go.

162
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:20,360
Let me.

163
00:09:20,719 --> 00:09:21,040
Okay.

164
00:09:22,839 --> 00:09:23,319
Thanks.

165
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:26,120
Don't listen to her nonsense.

166
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:27,799
Just be happy yourself.

167
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:28,959
Am I right?

168
00:09:29,839 --> 00:09:31,120
It's late. I'll hail a cab for you.

169
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,040
I've never

170
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:46,040
ridden a motorcycle before.

171
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:50,960
♪Sunlight falls through the curtains♪

172
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:53,920
♪Softly kissing your face♪

173
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:56,040
♪Like a secret♪

174
00:09:57,130 --> 00:09:59,240
♪A little secret♪

175
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:00,880
You want to take this motorcycle?

176
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:03,280
♪Whenever we're together♪

177
00:10:03,280 --> 00:10:06,160
♪It's the perfect time♪

178
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,490
♪A little understanding♪

179
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,800
♪Our bond growing deeper♪

180
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:15,880
♪When I look into your eyes♪

181
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:19,000
♪I see the stars shining♪

182
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:21,720
♪Listening to your heartbeat♪

183
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:24,320
♪Such a special rhythm♪

184
00:10:25,580 --> 00:10:27,120
♪I'm falling for you♪

185
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:34,170
♪Now baby I love you♪

186
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:40,040
♪And I just need you too♪

187
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:43,240
♪Every second♪

188
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:46,280
♪Every minute, every day♪

189
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:48,040
♪I want to be by your side♪

190
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:53,280
♪The moments that steal my heart♪

191
00:11:06,650 --> 00:11:09,720
♪Choosing where to have dinner♪

192
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:12,720
♪Or staying in all day♪

193
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:14,760
♪That's okay♪

194
00:11:15,740 --> 00:11:18,160
♪That's okay♪

195
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:22,280
♪Even our little disagreements♪

196
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:25,320
♪Are part of our love story♪

197
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:26,319
Thanks.

198
00:11:26,319 --> 00:11:27,640
♪Never letting go♪

199
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:30,199
♪Never letting go♪

200
00:11:30,199 --> 00:11:30,719
You're welcome.

201
00:11:32,220 --> 00:11:33,360
♪Through every changing season♪

202
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:33,799
Bye.

203
00:11:33,799 --> 00:11:34,640
♪Through every changing season♪

204
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:36,679
♪We've written a story of our own♪

205
00:11:36,679 --> 00:11:37,120
Bye.

206
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:40,920
♪And I still remember our promise♪

207
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:43,360
♪To explore the world♪

208
00:11:44,390 --> 00:11:46,640
♪Together♪

209
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:52,840
♪Now baby I love you♪

210
00:11:54,340 --> 00:11:59,320
♪And I just need you too♪

211
00:12:00,050 --> 00:12:02,440
♪Every second♪

212
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:05,400
♪Every minute, every day♪

213
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:07,040
♪I want to be by your side♪

214
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:12,610
♪The sweetest moments♪

215
00:12:23,319 --> 00:12:23,719
Dad,

216
00:12:24,319 --> 00:12:25,719
why do you take me here
to play the cello?

217
00:12:26,679 --> 00:12:28,120
I hope you can feel

218
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:29,400
that music is not limited

219
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:31,079
to time

220
00:12:31,079 --> 00:12:32,040
or space in this world.

221
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:33,280
No matter where it is played,

222
00:12:33,679 --> 00:12:34,839
it can be furious,

223
00:12:34,839 --> 00:12:35,520
joyful,

224
00:12:35,679 --> 00:12:37,280
remorseful, or sorrowful.

225
00:12:38,079 --> 00:12:39,120
Because you and your cello

226
00:12:39,959 --> 00:12:40,839
are both free.

227
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:43,000
(Song Youcheng)

228
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:44,959
(Sorry.)

229
00:13:45,199 --> 00:13:47,199
(The number you dialed is busy now.)

230
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:48,199
Not coming to work,

231
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,280
not asking for leave,

232
00:13:49,839 --> 00:13:51,040
and not answering the call.

233
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,000
What's this?

234
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:53,199
Rebelling?

235
00:13:57,599 --> 00:13:58,559
Among so many people,

236
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,360
no one could even lead

237
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:01,480
this tour group.

238
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:02,719
Mr. Song,

239
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:04,360
it's not that no one can lead them,

240
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:06,559
but Tong has led

241
00:14:06,959 --> 00:14:08,480
this senior tour group before.

242
00:14:08,919 --> 00:14:10,880
They said they were really happy
with Tong leading them.

243
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:12,280
That's why they have added

244
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:13,199
so many add-ons.

245
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:16,160
They specifically asked for Tong.

246
00:14:18,319 --> 00:14:18,959
You may leave now.

247
00:14:21,319 --> 00:14:22,040
Keep calling her.

248
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:23,400
If that doesn't work, go to her place.

249
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:24,520
Got it.

250
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:29,599
My master is a veteran employee

251
00:14:29,599 --> 00:14:30,679
at our agency.

252
00:14:30,839 --> 00:14:32,319
It's normal for her
to have a bit of a temper.

253
00:14:32,679 --> 00:14:33,640
After all,

254
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:35,160
sometimes, we need her

255
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,240
to push for performance, don't we?

256
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:37,400
What?

257
00:14:37,559 --> 00:14:38,880
Could such a big travel agency

258
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:39,640
not run smoothly

259
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:40,839
without Wen Yitong?

260
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:45,280
Mr. Song, please calm down.

261
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:47,439
It's not that this matter
can't be solved.

262
00:14:47,919 --> 00:14:48,799
I'll lead

263
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:49,839
this group.

264
00:14:50,439 --> 00:14:51,160
Last time my master

265
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:53,000
led this group, I was with her.

266
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:54,919
I know full well

267
00:14:54,919 --> 00:14:55,679
how to make

268
00:14:55,679 --> 00:14:57,360
these old people happy.

269
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,280
For something my master
can't bring herself to do,

270
00:15:00,599 --> 00:15:01,360
I can do it.

271
00:15:02,799 --> 00:15:04,280
For something she can
bring herself to do,

272
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:05,959
I can do it too.

273
00:15:08,199 --> 00:15:09,719
You truly have a honey tongue

274
00:15:09,799 --> 00:15:10,679
and a heart of gall.

275
00:15:10,959 --> 00:15:12,799
I don't actually hide my "gall."

276
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:15,280
I'm

277
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:16,880
open

278
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:18,839
and aboveboard.

279
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:23,230
(Wen Yitong)

280
00:15:26,319 --> 00:15:27,439
You want to get fired, huh?

281
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:29,599
You didn't answer my calls
or reply to my messages.

282
00:15:29,599 --> 00:15:30,480
And you're absent without leave.

283
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:31,520
What time is it now?

284
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:32,400
Just you wait.

285
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:33,400
You'll know the consequences
when you come.

286
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:34,559
I don't need to wait.

287
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:35,599
You wait there.

288
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:36,799
I'll go see you.

289
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:43,480
Crazy.

290
00:15:43,719 --> 00:15:44,719
This woman is insane.

291
00:15:44,959 --> 00:15:46,520
She actually hung up on me.

292
00:15:59,799 --> 00:16:00,439
Tong.

293
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:01,919
Master,

294
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:02,880
the group gathers at the Ferry Square.

295
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:03,679
Move aside.

296
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:05,199
Song Youcheng!

297
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:07,120
I quit!

298
00:16:09,439 --> 00:16:10,640
Have I been too lenient with you?

299
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:11,319
Do you have any idea

300
00:16:11,319 --> 00:16:12,240
how much trouble you've caused me?

301
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:13,120
Serving people is exhausting.

302
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:14,160
I'm done. I quit.

303
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:15,079
Why put on airs now?

304
00:16:15,079 --> 00:16:15,959
Who doesn't serve people?

305
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:16,760
I do, too!

306
00:16:16,799 --> 00:16:17,520
Let me tell you,

307
00:16:17,599 --> 00:16:18,839
if you can't reach the top,

308
00:16:18,839 --> 00:16:19,520
we're all the same,

309
00:16:19,520 --> 00:16:20,679
just serving others.

310
00:16:20,799 --> 00:16:22,319
Fine, even if you did reach the top,

311
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:23,400
when you were climbing up,

312
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:24,439
you'd only see their butts.

313
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:25,919
Only when you reach the top
and look down

314
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,160
do you see smiling faces.

315
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:32,199
Go on!

316
00:16:32,799 --> 00:16:33,360
Go find

317
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,439
a job not meant for serving people.

318
00:16:34,799 --> 00:16:35,719
Let me know when you find one.

319
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:36,839
I'll follow your lead.

320
00:16:37,880 --> 00:16:39,040
Putting on such an act with me!

321
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:40,400
You're really full-fledged, huh?

322
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:41,760
I'm not only full-fledged,

323
00:16:41,760 --> 00:16:43,040
but I've also found my backbone

324
00:16:43,079 --> 00:16:43,640
now.

325
00:16:43,719 --> 00:16:44,120
Are these

326
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:44,880
called turtle eggs?

327
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:46,679
Put it down!

328
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:48,240
I won't take it.

329
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:49,360
Who'd want your turtle eggs?

330
00:16:49,439 --> 00:16:50,839
I'm blessing you now.

331
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:51,919
May they hatch sooner,

332
00:16:51,959 --> 00:16:53,319
the group gathers at the Ferry Square.

333
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:54,000
I'll put it here safely.

334
00:16:54,079 --> 00:16:54,480
Keep it warm.

335
00:16:54,839 --> 00:16:55,280
Bye-bye.

336
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:00,120
- Master...
- Don't do this.

337
00:17:00,919 --> 00:17:01,880
Your nails are quite pretty.

338
00:17:01,919 --> 00:17:03,040
Don't break it.

339
00:17:05,079 --> 00:17:05,720
Don't follow me.

340
00:17:21,839 --> 00:17:22,799
Wait. Let me take a breather.

341
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:25,040
Take a minute before we go.

342
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:29,150
(Jiari International Travel Agency)

343
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,000
(Jiari International Travel Agency)
This place can be seen as

344
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,399
(Jiari International Travel Agency)
the starting point of making ends meet.

345
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,160
(Jiari International Travel Agency)

346
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,319
I just went step by step

347
00:17:33,359 --> 00:17:34,280
without stopping.

348
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,319
I even rubbed the skin off my heel.

349
00:17:39,639 --> 00:17:40,480
It healed later.

350
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,040
Then rubbed off again,
then healed again.

351
00:17:45,399 --> 00:17:46,399
In my bag or drawer,

352
00:17:46,399 --> 00:17:47,760
there are always some Band-Aids.

353
00:17:48,319 --> 00:17:49,480
I bought those top-tier ones

354
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:51,920
that don't curl up at the edges.

355
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:54,240
They stick on really tight.

356
00:17:55,760 --> 00:17:57,040
Later, calluses developed on my heels,

357
00:17:57,119 --> 00:17:57,920
and I felt no more pain.

358
00:18:00,599 --> 00:18:01,559
Jia said I had subdued

359
00:18:01,599 --> 00:18:02,520
those shoes.

360
00:18:07,119 --> 00:18:08,799
Fan Meijuan always reminds me

361
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:10,159
to be content with my life.

362
00:18:10,879 --> 00:18:11,520
I feel content.

363
00:18:11,599 --> 00:18:12,599
Even when I had no money
in my pocket,

364
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:13,720
I still felt content.

365
00:18:14,520 --> 00:18:15,599
A 15-yuan bowl of noodles

366
00:18:15,599 --> 00:18:16,960
is no different from a 150-yuan one.

367
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:18,960
A 30-yuan bag

368
00:18:19,399 --> 00:18:20,319
and a 300,000-yuan bag

369
00:18:20,319 --> 00:18:21,680
would just contain similar things,

370
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:22,760
like tissues and stuff.

371
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:24,879
I used to think like that.

372
00:18:26,359 --> 00:18:28,200
Now, there's 30 million in my house,

373
00:18:28,319 --> 00:18:29,440
but I still think that way.

374
00:18:30,639 --> 00:18:31,240
What's this called?

375
00:18:32,879 --> 00:18:34,399
Yu Ming,
that's called a poor man's mentality.

376
00:18:42,839 --> 00:18:43,680
After graduating from college,

377
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:44,599
I told myself,

378
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:46,399
"I'm going to live a rich life."

379
00:18:48,159 --> 00:18:49,240
Just a few years have passed,

380
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:53,159
yet I was smoothed out
and tamed by life.

381
00:18:54,119 --> 00:18:54,520
I got subdued.

382
00:18:55,879 --> 00:18:57,159
When you are used to being poor,

383
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:58,920
suddenly becoming rich

384
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:00,159
would just make you feel at a loss.

385
00:19:00,359 --> 00:19:00,960
You don't know what to do.

386
00:19:03,079 --> 00:19:04,240
You panic, getting all flustered.

387
00:19:06,639 --> 00:19:08,119
If you're willing,

388
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:11,000
you can transform into anything.

389
00:19:11,359 --> 00:19:12,480
Like the Monkey King,

390
00:19:13,079 --> 00:19:14,119
who has 72 transformations.

391
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:17,159
Let's go.

392
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:19,359
Let me take you to let off some steam.

393
00:19:20,079 --> 00:19:20,440
Let's go.

394
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:36,040
This shop looks nice.

395
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:37,079
Not bad.

396
00:19:37,960 --> 00:19:38,639
Pick something.

397
00:19:39,760 --> 00:19:40,559
This is men's wear.

398
00:19:41,639 --> 00:19:42,079
This one.

399
00:19:44,159 --> 00:19:44,960
This set looks good.

400
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,839
May I try this on in a size L?

401
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,079
I'm sorry, Miss.

402
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:49,760
Our new employee

403
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:50,960
has hung it in the wrong place.

404
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:51,879
It's fine

405
00:19:51,879 --> 00:19:52,720
if it's the wrong place.

406
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:53,599
Get her a size L to try on.

407
00:19:53,599 --> 00:19:54,079
Yeah.

408
00:19:54,359 --> 00:19:56,000
Sorry, sir. It's unavailable.

409
00:19:57,159 --> 00:19:58,000
What about size M?

410
00:19:58,319 --> 00:19:58,960
None of that, either.

411
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:00,159
Wait, what size is that set?

412
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:02,879
It's size L.

413
00:20:04,799 --> 00:20:06,000
Well, what do you mean?

414
00:20:07,599 --> 00:20:08,720
Here is the thing, sir.

415
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:10,240
Our brand has a regulation.

416
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:11,119
Your total expense

417
00:20:11,159 --> 00:20:12,720
must reach 200,000
to try those kinds of outfits on.

418
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:13,960
200,000?

419
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,639
Did you have to emphasize it that much?

420
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:19,639
Just go get it.

421
00:20:19,639 --> 00:20:20,359
It's you, Yitong?

422
00:20:20,359 --> 00:20:21,319
Let her try it on.

423
00:20:21,879 --> 00:20:22,440
Ms. Wang.

424
00:20:22,639 --> 00:20:23,520
You came too.

425
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:24,040
Why are you here?

426
00:20:24,040 --> 00:20:25,200
Just bring it over here.

427
00:20:25,399 --> 00:20:26,440
Sorry, sir.

428
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:27,680
Our company has a regulation.

429
00:20:27,799 --> 00:20:28,440
Only VIP members

430
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:30,119
can purchase the new-style items.

431
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:31,799
I don't think

432
00:20:31,799 --> 00:20:33,680
you're qualified for this right now.

433
00:20:33,839 --> 00:20:34,359
What about this?

434
00:20:34,359 --> 00:20:35,559
Am I qualified to purchase it now?

435
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:37,760
Can I become a VIP?

436
00:20:37,879 --> 00:20:38,960
Wait, what's going on here?

437
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,280
Now, people are spending money this way?

438
00:20:40,359 --> 00:20:41,480
You can't do business like this.

439
00:20:41,480 --> 00:20:41,879
No.

440
00:20:41,879 --> 00:20:42,520
I don't want it anymore.

441
00:20:42,520 --> 00:20:43,520
I don't like that outfit.

442
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:44,799
It's no big deal.

443
00:20:45,159 --> 00:20:45,960
I'm a VIP of your shop.

444
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:46,760
Which one did she want to try?

445
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:47,599
That one is ugly.

446
00:20:47,599 --> 00:20:48,399
That khaki color.

447
00:20:48,399 --> 00:20:49,680
I don't like that outfit.

448
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:50,480
I don't want to buy it.

449
00:20:50,760 --> 00:20:51,639
It's fine. Let her get it for you.

450
00:20:51,639 --> 00:20:52,359
It's no big deal.

451
00:20:52,639 --> 00:20:53,319
Go get it for her.

452
00:20:53,599 --> 00:20:54,159
Ms. Wang...

453
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:55,119
Yitong!

454
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:56,799
Yitong!

455
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:57,760
Look at you.

456
00:20:57,760 --> 00:20:59,119
You have no idea

457
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:00,720
how to do business.

458
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:02,240
You are so mean like this.

459
00:21:02,399 --> 00:21:03,200
Well, haven't you

460
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:04,319
lost a key account?

461
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:05,480
Our company has a regulation.

462
00:21:05,480 --> 00:21:06,240
What regulation?

463
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:07,720
You are just stupid.

464
00:21:07,799 --> 00:21:08,359
This way,

465
00:21:08,359 --> 00:21:09,559
you've lost a key account.

466
00:21:09,599 --> 00:21:10,159
Sir...

467
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,559
Please introduce your items to me.

468
00:21:14,599 --> 00:21:15,319
Is there anything new?

469
00:21:16,559 --> 00:21:17,799
I thought you went to the toilet.

470
00:21:18,839 --> 00:21:20,399
That salesgirl is so mean.

471
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:21,159
She

472
00:21:21,159 --> 00:21:22,280
was picking on us.

473
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:23,200
But I scolded her.

474
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:24,159
Did you put the money safely?

475
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:24,680
It's safe here.

476
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:25,680
She has lost a key account.

477
00:21:25,879 --> 00:21:26,399
Let me tell you,

478
00:21:26,399 --> 00:21:27,639
we're reeking a kind of smell now.

479
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:28,159
What smell?

480
00:21:28,399 --> 00:21:28,960
The smell of poverty.

481
00:21:29,159 --> 00:21:31,200
We'll get rid of it with money then.

482
00:21:31,559 --> 00:21:32,799
Continue our 72 transformations.

483
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:43,840
♪Rolling in cash♪

484
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:46,320
♪Rolling in cash♪

485
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:48,460
♪Rolling in cash♪

486
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:50,640
♪Rolling in cash♪

487
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:57,360
♪Rolling in cash♪

488
00:21:58,150 --> 00:21:59,600
♪Rolling in cash♪

489
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:01,760
♪Rolling in cash♪

490
00:22:02,470 --> 00:22:03,920
♪Rolling in cash♪

491
00:22:10,399 --> 00:22:11,040
Comfortable?

492
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:12,559
Too small.

493
00:22:13,079 --> 00:22:13,599
It doesn't matter.

494
00:22:13,879 --> 00:22:14,520
There are bigger ones.

495
00:22:15,119 --> 00:22:16,000
Pack them all.

496
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:29,720
Bro,

497
00:22:30,079 --> 00:22:31,359
you have no idea.

498
00:22:31,799 --> 00:22:33,159
It was a bag full of banknotes.

499
00:22:33,159 --> 00:22:34,000
A sea of red!

500
00:22:34,359 --> 00:22:35,680
Wen Yitong's foolish husband

501
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:36,920
just poured it all on the table.

502
00:22:37,079 --> 00:22:38,839
A large pile, you know.

503
00:22:39,079 --> 00:22:40,599
He was forcing them

504
00:22:40,839 --> 00:22:41,799
to take it.

505
00:22:42,119 --> 00:22:43,559
He must have been chosen

506
00:22:43,559 --> 00:22:44,520
by the God of Wealth.

507
00:22:52,319 --> 00:22:54,240
I was wondering why she chose to quit.

508
00:22:57,520 --> 00:22:58,399
She has really

509
00:22:58,399 --> 00:23:00,079
climbed to the top of the pyramid.

510
00:23:10,639 --> 00:23:11,760
I can't see anything.

511
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:13,440
Something must be hidden inside.

512
00:23:14,159 --> 00:23:15,599
Otherwise, why would he
seal the windows?

513
00:23:23,920 --> 00:23:24,599
Bro.

514
00:23:28,520 --> 00:23:28,960
Look,

515
00:23:30,119 --> 00:23:31,200
what's that?

516
00:23:33,119 --> 00:23:34,399
A bill validator.

517
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:48,359
Weijie,

518
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:50,040
are you done?

519
00:23:50,119 --> 00:23:50,879
Right away. Well...

520
00:23:51,040 --> 00:23:52,119
I need to make a call first.

521
00:23:52,359 --> 00:23:53,480
Hurry up. It's too hot.

522
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:05,200
♪Work hard and make money♪

523
00:24:05,319 --> 00:24:06,639
♪I want to get rich♪

524
00:24:07,159 --> 00:24:08,799
(Cousin Qian Weijie)
♪A villa by the sea♪

525
00:24:08,960 --> 00:24:09,680
♪Seafood every day♪

526
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:10,359
Hello.

527
00:24:10,559 --> 00:24:11,159
Yu Ming,

528
00:24:11,520 --> 00:24:12,359
where are you?

529
00:24:12,879 --> 00:24:13,760
It doesn't matter where you are.

530
00:24:13,879 --> 00:24:15,000
I'm taking my kid out for some fun.

531
00:24:15,040 --> 00:24:16,200
But my car broke down on the way.

532
00:24:16,359 --> 00:24:17,200
Bring some tools

533
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:18,040
and come help me fix it.

534
00:24:19,520 --> 00:24:20,040
I won't go.

535
00:24:20,319 --> 00:24:21,280
I'll cover your fuel cost.

536
00:24:21,399 --> 00:24:22,520
I'll transfer 200 yuan to you.

537
00:24:22,520 --> 00:24:22,960
Is that okay?

538
00:24:23,720 --> 00:24:25,000
I'll give you 300, but I won't go.

539
00:24:25,799 --> 00:24:26,839
Are you being

540
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:28,000
rebellious with me today or what?

541
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,040
I just won't go!

542
00:24:40,440 --> 00:24:41,480
I didn't make it perfect,

543
00:24:43,159 --> 00:24:43,639
did I?

544
00:24:44,599 --> 00:24:45,440
You didn't sound decisive enough.

545
00:24:45,760 --> 00:24:46,200
Yeah.

546
00:24:46,599 --> 00:24:48,079
I wanted to let off some steam to him.

547
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:50,720
But as I was often
being ordered around by him,

548
00:24:50,799 --> 00:24:52,639
I was suddenly at a loss for words.

549
00:24:54,599 --> 00:24:55,639
It's fine. You'll get better gradually.

550
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:56,480
I, Monkey King,

551
00:24:57,599 --> 00:25:00,079
have intimidated the Heavenly court
in an imposing manner.

552
00:25:00,399 --> 00:25:01,119
No one dares to challenge

553
00:25:02,159 --> 00:25:05,599
the Golden Cudgel
with unstoppable force.

554
00:25:06,040 --> 00:25:08,240
Battle drums sound above the clouds.

555
00:25:08,639 --> 00:25:14,280
I will turn the world upside down.

556
00:25:15,960 --> 00:25:16,839
What are you doing? Let's go.

557
00:25:26,119 --> 00:25:28,319
I want to invite Aunt's family

558
00:25:29,159 --> 00:25:30,119
to dinner.

559
00:25:34,799 --> 00:25:35,200
Okay.

560
00:25:41,599 --> 00:25:42,159
Hello, Mom.

561
00:25:42,879 --> 00:25:44,599
Yu Ming wants to invite us
to dinner this evening.

562
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:47,680
What else could it be for?

563
00:25:48,599 --> 00:25:49,280
It must be because

564
00:25:49,280 --> 00:25:50,319
he feels guilty towards me

565
00:25:50,319 --> 00:25:51,319
and wants to make up for it.

566
00:25:53,159 --> 00:25:54,879
Fine,
we'll head straight to the restaurant

567
00:25:54,879 --> 00:25:55,399
in the evening.

568
00:25:56,359 --> 00:25:56,720
Okay.

569
00:25:58,559 --> 00:25:59,359
What's up, darling?

570
00:25:59,839 --> 00:26:00,680
Who's treating us to dinner?

571
00:26:01,319 --> 00:26:01,839
Yu Ming

572
00:26:02,639 --> 00:26:03,839
wants to treat our family to dinner.

573
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:05,520
He said it's not spacious

574
00:26:05,639 --> 00:26:06,399
enough at home,

575
00:26:06,520 --> 00:26:07,359
so he wants to dine out.

576
00:26:07,559 --> 00:26:08,879
Yu Ming is treating us?

577
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:10,319
And we're dining out?

578
00:26:11,319 --> 00:26:12,960
What show is he putting on here?

579
00:26:19,079 --> 00:26:20,079
Elegant Garden?

580
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:22,200
That's right. Elegant Garden.

581
00:26:23,599 --> 00:26:24,200
Waitress,

582
00:26:24,319 --> 00:26:25,280
may I ask

583
00:26:25,559 --> 00:26:26,839
where the Ascension Room is?

584
00:26:27,319 --> 00:26:28,040
Go straight ahead,

585
00:26:28,079 --> 00:26:29,319
then up the spiral staircase
to the second floor.

586
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:31,440
This place

587
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:32,559
is known

588
00:26:32,599 --> 00:26:33,399
for 1,000 yuan a bite.

589
00:26:34,799 --> 00:26:35,319
Mom,

590
00:26:35,839 --> 00:26:36,879
could he plan

591
